Facts & Figures: China's Exports to U.S. in First Quarter 
Following are the latest facts and figures on China's major export
commodities to the United States in the first quarter of 2000, provided
by the General Administration of Customs:
-- Export of machines, electronic goods, audiovisual equipment and
relevant parts and accessories was 3.263 billion U.S. dollars.
-- Export of shoes, hats, umbrellas, feather, down and products,
artificial flowers was 1.356 billion U.S. dollars.
-- Export of textile materials and products was 878.424 million U.S.
dollars.
-- Export of base metals and related products was 698.278 million U.S.
dollars.
-- Export of plastics, rubber and related products was 553.459 million
U.S. dollars.
